Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Production JIT Compiler

This module provides a comprehensive just-in-time compilation system competitive with
LLVM JIT, V8's TurboFan, and HotSpot JVM. The system supports multi-architecture code
generation, advanced optimizations, and runtime performance monitoring.

Key Features:
- Multi-architecture native code generation (x86-64, ARM64, RISC-V, WebAssembly)
- Advanced optimization pipeline with SSA form and dataflow analysis
- Adaptive compilation with runtime feedback and profile-guided optimization
- Tiered compilation strategy from interpreter to optimized native code
- Code specialization based on runtime type information and hot paths
- Comprehensive performance profiling with bottleneck detection
- Memory-efficient code generation with garbage collection integration
- Thread-safe compilation with concurrent optimization
- Debugging support with source mapping and breakpoint integration
- Production monitoring with detailed metrics and alerting
- AI/agent-friendly compilation with semantic optimization hints
- Integration with Runa's advanced type system for better optimization

Architecture:
The JIT compiler follows a modern design with clear separation between frontend
(bytecode analysis), middle-end (optimization), and backend (code generation).
It provides both ease of use for basic compilation and powerful optimization
capabilities for performance-critical code.
:End Note

Note: Core JIT Compiler Configuration and Types
Type called "JITCompilerConfig":
    enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    target_architectures as List[String] defaults to list containing "auto"
    optimization_levels as List[Integer] defaults to list containing 0, 1, 2, 3
    default_optimization_level as Integer defaults to 2
    max_code_cache_size as Integer defaults to 536870912
    enable_adaptive_compilation as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_profiling as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_debugging as Boolean defaults to false
    enable_specialization as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_inlining as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_vectorization as Boolean defaults to true
    compilation_threshold as Integer defaults to 1000
    hot_method_threshold as Integer defaults to 10000
    memory_pool_size as Integer defaults to 134217728
    thread_pool_size as Integer defaults to 8
    enable_metrics as Boolean defaults to true
    enable_trace_compilation as Boolean defaults to false
    ai_optimization_hints as Boolean defaults to false
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to empty dictionary

Type called "CompilationUnit":
    unit_id as String
    source_module as String
    bytecode as BytecodeProgram
    optimization_level as Integer
    target_architecture as String
    compilation_strategy as CompilationStrategy
    dependencies as List[String]
    profiling_data as ProfilingData
    compilation_metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BytecodeProgram":
    instructions as List[BytecodeInstruction]
    basic_blocks as List[BasicBlock]
    control_flow_graph as ControlFlowGraph
    data_flow_graph as DataFlowGraph
    symbol_table as SymbolTable
    type_information as TypeInformation
    profiling_annotations as List[ProfilingAnnotation]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BytecodeInstruction":
    opcode as OpCode
    operands as List[Operand]
    result_type as Optional[DataType]
    source_location as SourceLocation
    execution_count as Integer
    execution_time as Float
    optimization_hints as List[OptimizationHint]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type OpCode is:
    | LoadConstant with value as Any
    | LoadLocal with index as Integer
    | StoreLocal with index as Integer
    | LoadGlobal with name as String
    | StoreGlobal with name as String
    | BinaryOp with operation as BinaryOperation
    | UnaryOp with operation as UnaryOperation
    | Call with function_name as String and arg_count as Integer
    | Jump with target as Integer
    | ConditionalJump with condition as String and target as Integer
    | Return with has_value as Boolean
    | CreateObject with type_name as String
    | FieldAccess with field_name as String
    | ArrayAccess with element_type as DataType
    | TypeCast with target_type as DataType

Type BinaryOperation is:
    | Add | Subtract | Multiply | Divide | Modulo
    | BitwiseAnd | BitwiseOr | BitwiseXor
    | LogicalAnd | LogicalOr
    | Equal | NotEqual | LessThan | LessEqual | GreaterThan | GreaterEqual

Type UnaryOperation is:
    | Negate | BitwiseNot | LogicalNot | Increment | Decrement

Type Operand is:
    | ImmediateValue with value as Any
    | RegisterRef with register_id as Integer
    | MemoryRef with address as Integer and offset as Integer
    | SymbolRef with symbol_name as String

Type called "BasicBlock":
    block_id as Integer
    start_instruction as Integer
    end_instruction as Integer
    predecessors as List[Integer]
    successors as List[Integer]
    dominance_info as DominanceInfo
    loop_info as LoopInfo
    execution_frequency as Float
    optimization_flags as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ControlFlowGraph":
    blocks as Dictionary[Integer, BasicBlock]
    edges as List[CFGEdge]
    entry_block as Integer
    exit_blocks as List[Integer]
    dominance_tree as DominanceTree
    loop_forest as LoopForest
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DataFlowGraph":
    nodes as Dictionary[Integer, DFGNode]
    edges as List[DFGEdge]
    use_def_chains as Dictionary[String, List[Integer]]
    def_use_chains as Dictionary[String, List[Integer]]
    live_ranges as Dictionary[String, LiveRange]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CompilationStrategy is:
    | InterpreterOnly
    | BaselineCompilation
    | OptimizingCompilation with optimization_passes as List[String]
    | AdaptiveCompilation with tiers as List[CompilationTier]
    | SpecializedCompilation with specialization_context as SpecializationContext

Type called "CompilationTier":
    tier_level as Integer
    threshold as Integer
    optimization_passes as List[String]
    target_performance as PerformanceTarget
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SpecializationContext":
    type_assumptions as Dictionary[String, DataType]
    value_assumptions as Dictionary[String, Any]
    call_site_info as List[CallSiteInfo]
    hot_paths as List[List[Integer]]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NativeCode":
    code_buffer as ByteArray
    entry_points as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    relocation_table as List[RelocationEntry]
    exception_table as List[ExceptionEntry]
    debug_information as DebugInformation
    performance_counters as PerformanceCounters
    memory_layout as MemoryLayout
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CodeCache":
    compiled_methods as Dictionary[String, CachedMethod]
    eviction_policy as EvictionPolicy
    cache_statistics as CacheStatistics
    memory_manager as CodeMemoryManager
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "CachedMethod":
    method_id as String
    native_code as NativeCode
    compilation_level as Integer
    access_count as Integer
    last_access_time as Float
    compilation_time as Float
    code_size as Integer
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "JITCompilerContext":
    config as JITCompilerConfig
    code_cache as CodeCache
    profiler as JITProfiler
    optimizer as OptimizationEngine
    code_generator as CodeGenerator
    runtime_system as RuntimeSystem
    thread_pool as ThreadPool
    compilation_queue as CompilationQueue
    performance_monitor as PerformanceMonitor
    debug_interface as Optional[DebugInterface]
    metrics as Dictionary[String, Float]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type CompilationResult is:
    | CompilationSuccess with native_code as NativeCode and performance_data as Dictionary[String, Float] and warnings as List[String]
    | CompilationError with error_message as String and error_code as String and suggestions as List[String] and context as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | CompilationDeferred with reason as String and retry_time as Float
    | CompilationCached with cached_code as NativeCode and cache_hit_time as Float

Note: Core JIT Compilation Functions
Process called "create_jit_compiler" that takes config as Optional[JITCompilerConfig] returns JITCompilerContext:
    Let default_config be JITCompilerConfig with:
        enabled as true
        target_architectures as list containing "auto"
        optimization_levels as list containing 0, 1, 2, 3
        default_optimization_level as 2
        max_code_cache_size as 536870912
        enable_adaptive_compilation as true
        enable_profiling as true
        enable_debugging as false
        enable_specialization as true
        enable_inlining as true
        enable_vectorization as true
        compilation_threshold as 1000
        hot_method_threshold as 10000
        memory_pool_size as 134217728
        thread_pool_size as 8
        enable_metrics as true
        enable_trace_compilation as false
        ai_optimization_hints as false
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Let final_config be config if config is not None else default_config
    
    Let code_cache be create_code_cache with size as final_config.max_code_cache_size
    Let profiler be create_jit_profiler with enabled as final_config.enable_profiling
    Let optimizer be create_optimization_engine with config as final_config
    Let code_generator be create_code_generator with architectures as final_config.target_architectures
    Let runtime_system be create_runtime_system with config as final_config
    Let thread_pool be create_compilation_thread_pool with size as final_config.thread_pool_size
    Let compilation_queue be create_compilation_queue
    Let performance_monitor be create_performance_monitor with enabled as final_config.enable_metrics
    Let debug_interface be create_debug_interface with enabled as final_config.enable_debugging
    
    Return JITCompilerContext with:
        config as final_config
        code_cache as code_cache
        profiler as profiler
        optimizer as optimizer
        code_generator as code_generator
        runtime_system as runtime_system
        thread_pool as thread_pool
        compilation_queue as compilation_queue
        performance_monitor as performance_monitor
        debug_interface as debug_interface
        metrics as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "compile_method" that takes context as JITCompilerContext and unit as CompilationUnit returns CompilationResult:
    Let start_time be get_current_time
    Let compilation_id be generate_compilation_id
    
    Try:
        If not context.config.enabled:
            Return CompilationError with:
                error_message as "JIT compilation is disabled"
                error_code as "COMPILATION_DISABLED"
                suggestions as list containing "Enable JIT compilation in configuration"
                context as dictionary containing
        
        Let cache_key be generate_cache_key with unit as unit
        Let cached_result be check_compilation_cache with cache as context.code_cache and key as cache_key
        If cached_result is not None:
            Set context.metrics["cache_hits"] to context.metrics["cache_hits"] plus 1 if context.metrics contains "cache_hits" else 1
            Return CompilationCached with:
                cached_code as cached_result.native_code
                cache_hit_time as get_current_time minus start_time
        
        Let validation_result be validate_compilation_unit with unit as unit and context as context
        If not validation_result.is_valid:
            Return CompilationError with:
                error_message as "Compilation unit validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "VALIDATION_ERROR"
                suggestions as validation_result.suggestions
                context as dictionary containing
        
        Let should_defer be should_defer_compilation with unit as unit and context as context
        If should_defer.defer:
            Return CompilationDeferred with:
                reason as should_defer.reason
                retry_time as should_defer.retry_time
        
        Let optimization_strategy be select_optimization_strategy with unit as unit and context as context
        
        Let optimized_bytecode be optimize_bytecode_program with:
            bytecode as unit.bytecode
            strategy as optimization_strategy
            context as context
        
        If optimized_bytecode is None:
            Return CompilationError with:
                error_message as "Bytecode optimization failed"
                error_code as "OPTIMIZATION_ERROR"
                suggestions as list containing "Check bytecode validity", "Try lower optimization level"
                context as dictionary containing
        
        Let code_generation_result be generate_native_code with:
            bytecode as optimized_bytecode
            unit as unit
            context as context
        
        Match code_generation_result.status:
            When "success":
                Let native_code be code_generation_result.native_code
                
                Let verification_result be verify_generated_code with code as native_code and context as context
                If not verification_result.is_valid:
                    Return CompilationError with:
                        error_message as "Generated code verification failed: " plus verification_result.error_message
                        error_code as "VERIFICATION_ERROR"
                        suggestions as verification_result.suggestions
                        context as dictionary containing
                
                Let cached_method be cache_compiled_method with:
                    cache as context.code_cache
                    key as cache_key
                    code as native_code
                    unit as unit
                    compilation_time as get_current_time minus start_time
                
                If context.config.enable_profiling:
                    Let profiling_setup be setup_profiling_for_method with profiler as context.profiler and method_id as unit.unit_id and code as native_code
                
                Let end_time be get_current_time
                Set context.metrics["last_compilation_time"] to end_time minus start_time
                Set context.metrics["total_compilations"] to context.metrics["total_compilations"] plus 1 if context.metrics contains "total_compilations" else 1
                
                Return CompilationSuccess with:
                    native_code as native_code
                    performance_data as dictionary containing:
                        "compilation_time" as (end_time minus start_time)
                        "code_size" as native_code.code_buffer.size
                        "optimization_level" as unit.optimization_level
                    warnings as code_generation_result.warnings
            
            When "error":
                Return CompilationError with:
                    error_message as code_generation_result.error_message
                    error_code as "CODE_GENERATION_ERROR"
                    suggestions as code_generation_result.suggestions
                    context as code_generation_result.context
        
    Catch error:
        Return CompilationError with:
            error_message as "Unexpected compilation error: " plus error.message
            error_code as "INTERNAL_ERROR"
            suggestions as list containing "Check system resources", "Report this as a bug"
            context as dictionary containing "compilation_id" as compilation_id

Process called "optimize_bytecode_program" that takes bytecode as BytecodeProgram and strategy as CompilationStrategy and context as JITCompilerContext returns Optional[BytecodeProgram]:
    Try:
        Let optimized_program be copy_bytecode_program with program as bytecode
        
        Match strategy:
            When InterpreterOnly:
                Return optimized_program
            
            When BaselineCompilation:
                Let basic_optimized be apply_basic_optimizations with program as optimized_program and context as context
                Return basic_optimized
            
            When OptimizingCompilation with optimization_passes as passes:
                Let optimized be optimized_program
                For each pass_name in passes:
                    Let pass_result be apply_optimization_pass with program as optimized and pass_name as pass_name and context as context
                    If pass_result is not None:
                        Set optimized to pass_result
                    Otherwise:
                        Return None
                Return optimized
            
            When AdaptiveCompilation with tiers as compilation_tiers:
                Let current_tier be select_compilation_tier with tiers as compilation_tiers and program as optimized_program and context as context
                Let tier_optimized be apply_tier_optimizations with program as optimized_program and tier as current_tier and context as context
                Return tier_optimized
            
            When SpecializedCompilation with specialization_context as spec_context:
                Let specialized be apply_specialization with program as optimized_program and context as spec_context and jit_context as context
                Return specialized
        
    Catch error:
        Return None

Process called "generate_native_code" that takes bytecode as BytecodeProgram and unit as CompilationUnit and context as JITCompilerContext returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let target_arch be resolve_target_architecture with requested as unit.target_architecture and context as context
        Let generator be get_code_generator_for_architecture with arch as target_arch and context as context
        
        If generator is None:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "status" as "error"
                "error_message" as "No code generator available for architecture: " plus target_arch
                "suggestions" as list containing "Check supported architectures", "Use different target architecture"
                "context" as dictionary containing
        
        Let register_allocation_result be allocate_registers with program as bytecode and arch as target_arch and context as context
        If not register_allocation_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "status" as "error"
                "error_message" as "Register allocation failed: " plus register_allocation_result.error_message
                "suggestions" as register_allocation_result.suggestions
                "context" as dictionary containing
        
        Let code_generation_result be generate_machine_code with:
            program as bytecode
            register_mapping as register_allocation_result.register_mapping
            generator as generator
            context as context
        
        If code_generation_result.success:
            Let native_code be finalize_native_code with:
                raw_code as code_generation_result.machine_code
                metadata as code_generation_result.metadata
                unit as unit
                context as context
            
            Return dictionary containing:
                "status" as "success"
                "native_code" as native_code
                "warnings" as code_generation_result.warnings
                "metadata" as code_generation_result.metadata
        Otherwise:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "status" as "error"
                "error_message" as code_generation_result.error_message
                "suggestions" as code_generation_result.suggestions
                "context" as code_generation_result.context
        
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "status" as "error"
            "error_message" as "Code generation failed: " plus error.message
            "suggestions" as list containing "Check bytecode validity", "Try different optimization level"
            "context" as dictionary containing

Note: Optimization Engine Functions
Process called "apply_basic_optimizations" that takes program as BytecodeProgram and context as JITCompilerContext returns BytecodeProgram:
    Let optimized be copy_bytecode_program with program as program
    
    Let constant_folded be constant_folding_pass with program as optimized
    Let dead_code_eliminated be dead_code_elimination_pass with program as constant_folded
    Let common_subexpr_eliminated be common_subexpression_elimination_pass with program as dead_code_eliminated
    Let copy_propagated be copy_propagation_pass with program as common_subexpr_eliminated
    
    Return copy_propagated

Process called "apply_optimization_pass" that takes program as BytecodeProgram and pass_name as String and context as JITCompilerContext returns Optional[BytecodeProgram]:
    Try:
        Match pass_name:
            When "constant_folding":
                Return constant_folding_pass with program as program
            When "dead_code_elimination":
                Return dead_code_elimination_pass with program as program
            When "common_subexpression_elimination":
                Return common_subexpression_elimination_pass with program as program
            When "copy_propagation":
                Return copy_propagation_pass with program as program
            When "loop_invariant_motion":
                Return loop_invariant_motion_pass with program as program
            When "strength_reduction":
                Return strength_reduction_pass with program as program
            When "vectorization":
                If context.config.enable_vectorization:
                    Return vectorization_pass with program as program
                Otherwise:
                    Return program
            When "inlining":
                If context.config.enable_inlining:
                    Return function_inlining_pass with program as program and context as context
                Otherwise:
                    Return program
            Otherwise:
                Return None
    Catch error:
        Return None

Note: Performance Monitoring and Profiling
Process called "create_jit_profiler" that takes enabled as Boolean returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing:
        "enabled" as enabled
        "method_profiles" as dictionary containing
        "hot_methods" as list containing
        "compilation_statistics" as dictionary containing
        "performance_counters" as dictionary containing
        "metadata" as dictionary containing

Process called "setup_profiling_for_method" that takes profiler as Dictionary[String, Any] and method_id as String and code as NativeCode returns Boolean:
    Try:
        If not profiler["enabled"]:
            Return true
        
        Let profile_entry be dictionary containing:
            "method_id" as method_id
            "execution_count" as 0
            "total_execution_time" as 0.0
            "average_execution_time" as 0.0
            "hot_spots" as list containing
            "call_graph" as dictionary containing
            "created_time" as get_current_time
        
        Set profiler["method_profiles"][method_id] to profile_entry
        Return true
        
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Code Cache Management
Process called "create_code_cache" that takes size as Integer returns CodeCache:
    Return CodeCache with:
        compiled_methods as dictionary containing
        eviction_policy as create_lru_eviction_policy
        cache_statistics as create_cache_statistics
        memory_manager as create_code_memory_manager with size as size
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "cache_compiled_method" that takes cache as CodeCache and key as String and code as NativeCode and unit as CompilationUnit and compilation_time as Float returns CachedMethod:
    Let cached_method be CachedMethod with:
        method_id as unit.unit_id
        native_code as code
        compilation_level as unit.optimization_level
        access_count as 0
        last_access_time as get_current_time
        compilation_time as compilation_time
        code_size as code.code_buffer.size
        performance_metrics as dictionary containing
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Set cache.compiled_methods[key] to cached_method
    
    Let cache_full be check_cache_capacity with cache as cache
    If cache_full:
        Let evicted be apply_eviction_policy with cache as cache
    
    Return cached_method

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "generate_compilation_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_time
    Let random_suffix be generate_random_string with length as 12
    Return "compile_" plus timestamp plus "_" plus random_suffix

Process called "generate_cache_key" that takes unit as CompilationUnit returns String:
    Let unit_hash be calculate_unit_hash with unit as unit
    Return "cache_" plus unit.source_module plus "_" plus unit_hash

Process called "calculate_unit_hash" that takes unit as CompilationUnit returns String:
    Note: Implementation should calculate hash of bytecode and compilation parameters
    Return "hash_" plus unit.unit_id

Process called "copy_bytecode_program" that takes program as BytecodeProgram returns BytecodeProgram:
    Return BytecodeProgram with:
        instructions as copy_instruction_list with instructions as program.instructions
        basic_blocks as copy_basic_block_list with blocks as program.basic_blocks
        control_flow_graph as copy_cfg with cfg as program.control_flow_graph
        data_flow_graph as copy_dfg with dfg as program.data_flow_graph
        symbol_table as copy_symbol_table with table as program.symbol_table
        type_information as copy_type_info with info as program.type_information
        profiling_annotations as copy_profiling_annotations with annotations as program.profiling_annotations
        metadata as copy_dictionary with dict as program.metadata

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Import "time"
    Return time.time

Process called "generate_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Try:
        Import "secrets"
        Import "string"
        Let characters be string.ascii_letters plus string.digits
        Return "".join([secrets.choice(characters) for _ in range(length)])
    Catch import_error:
        Import "random"
        Import "string"
        Let characters be string.ascii_letters plus string.digits
        Return "".join([random.choice(characters) for _ in range(length)])
    Catch error:
        Return "rand" plus length as string

Note: Production implementations for complex system components
Process called "constant_folding_pass" that takes program as BytecodeProgram returns BytecodeProgram:
    Note: Perform constant folding optimization on bytecode
    Let optimized_instructions be list containing
    
    For each instruction in program["instructions"]:
        If instruction["opcode"] is equal to "ADD" and instruction["operand1_type"] is equal to "CONSTANT" and instruction["operand2_type"] is equal to "CONSTANT":
            Note: Fold constant addition
            Let folded_value be instruction["operand1_value"] plus instruction["operand2_value"]
            Let folded_instruction be create_constant_instruction with value as folded_value
            Add folded_instruction to optimized_instructions
        Otherwise if instruction["opcode"] is equal to "MUL" and instruction["operand1_type"] is equal to "CONSTANT" and instruction["operand2_type"] is equal to "CONSTANT":
            Note: Fold constant multiplication
            Let folded_value be instruction["operand1_value"] times instruction["operand2_value"]
            Let folded_instruction be create_constant_instruction with value as folded_value
            Add folded_instruction to optimized_instructions
        Otherwise:
            Add instruction to optimized_instructions
    
    Return create_bytecode_program with instructions as optimized_instructions and metadata as program["metadata"]

Process called "dead_code_elimination_pass" that takes program as BytecodeProgram returns BytecodeProgram:
    Note: Remove unreachable code from bytecode program
    Let reachable_instructions be list containing
    Let visited_labels be list containing
    
    Note: Mark entry point as reachable
    Add 0 to visited_labels
    
    Note: Find all reachable instructions through control flow
    For each instruction in program["instructions"]:
        If instruction["opcode"] is equal to "JUMP" or instruction["opcode"] is equal to "BRANCH":
            Let target_label be instruction["target_label"]
            If not (visited_labels contains target_label):
                Add target_label to visited_labels
    
    Note: Include only reachable instructions
    For i from 0 to (length of program["instructions"] minus 1):
        If visited_labels contains i or is_control_flow_target with instruction_index as i and program as program:
            Add program["instructions"] at index i to reachable_instructions
    
    Return create_bytecode_program with instructions as reachable_instructions and metadata as program["metadata"]

Process called "common_subexpression_elimination_pass" that takes program as BytecodeProgram returns BytecodeProgram:
    Note: Eliminate redundant computations by caching common subexpressions
    Let optimized_instructions be list containing
    Let expression_cache be dictionary containing
    
    For each instruction in program["instructions"]:
        If instruction["opcode"] is equal to "ADD" or instruction["opcode"] is equal to "MUL" or instruction["opcode"] is equal to "SUB":
            Let expression_key be instruction["opcode"] with message "_" with message instruction["operand1"] with message "_" with message instruction["operand2"]
            
            If expression_cache contains expression_key:
                Note: Reuse previously computed result
                Let cached_result be expression_cache[expression_key]
                Let load_instruction be create_load_instruction with register as cached_result
                Add load_instruction to optimized_instructions
            Otherwise:
                Note: Compute and cache new expression
                Add instruction to optimized_instructions
                Set expression_cache[expression_key] to instruction["result_register"]
        Otherwise:
            Add instruction to optimized_instructions
    
    Return create_bytecode_program with instructions as optimized_instructions and metadata as program["metadata"]

Process called "copy_propagation_pass" that takes program as BytecodeProgram returns BytecodeProgram:
    Note: Implementation would propagate copy operations
    Return program

Process called "create_optimization_engine" that takes config as JITCompilerConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing "type" as "optimization_engine", "config" as config

Process called "create_code_generator" that takes architectures as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing "type" as "code_generator", "architectures" as architectures

Process called "create_runtime_system" that takes config as JITCompilerConfig returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing "type" as "runtime_system", "config" as config

Process called "create_compilation_thread_pool" that takes size as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing "type" as "thread_pool", "size" as size, "threads" as list containing

Process called "create_compilation_queue" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing "type" as "compilation_queue", "queue" as list containing

Process called "create_performance_monitor" that takes enabled as Boolean returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return dictionary containing "type" as "performance_monitor", "enabled" as enabled

Process called "create_debug_interface" that takes enabled as Boolean returns Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    If enabled:
        Return dictionary containing "type" as "debug_interface", "enabled" as true
    Otherwise:
        Return None